<item>
            <title>[SOLR-16584] integrationTests (BATS) fail on GitHub and Jenkins</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16584</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I discovered during my work on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16475&quot; title=&quot;Ability to change the default replica placement plugin though sysProp&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-16475&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-16475&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/solr/pull/1089&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;PR&lt;/a&gt;) that BATS tests run by &lt;tt&gt;./gradlew integrationTests&lt;/tt&gt; failed consistently in GitHub, even if they always pass locally on my mac.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=krisden&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;krisden&quot;&gt;krisden&lt;/a&gt; followed up with &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/solr/pull/1223&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/solr/pull/1223&lt;/a&gt; on main since my initial PR included some changes to BATS itself. It also failed on main.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Relizing we do not run nightly integrationTest in Jenkins, I added &lt;tt&gt;integrationTests&lt;/tt&gt; task to the regular &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Solr/job/Solr-Check-main/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Solr-Check-Main&lt;/a&gt; Jenkins job, and it now fails the same way as GitHub action does, except for &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Solr/job/Solr-Check-main/5544/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;one run&lt;/a&gt;&#160;that passed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
